<L>__{exterior hill house driveway day}
<A>__{the car rumbles up the drive toward the carport.}
<L>__{interior nell's car day}
<A>__{nell stops the car in front of the entrance, right inside the carport. in the silence all we can hear is her breathing.}
<L>__{exterior hill house day}
<A>__{her car sits in front of the house, tiny, alone. its brake lights go off. the finger like pillars of the car port seem like a hand pinning the car in place under the house's gaze. nell gets out of the car. nell stares, daunted... yet there is something about the house. a romance in its lilac heavy gothic decay. nell feels it, is drawn to it.}
